Family, friends and followers will bid farewell to former veteran broadcaster Winnie MahlanguÂ on Thursday. Her funeral service takes place at St Albans Cathedral in Pretoria. She will be buried at the Pretoria East Cemetery. The SABC has described Mahlangu, who passed away at the age of 88, as a pioneer in the industry. Mahlangu who was affectionately known as Mafungwase, joined the public broadcaster as the first black woman broadcaster at the erstwhile Radio Bantu in 1962. She retired from the corporation in 1993. In the video below, Mahlangu has been described as a pillar of strength in the broadcasting industry: 